<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Sim_OffTheGrid" s="240246">
  <T n="category">10175<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_SimLife--></T>
  <T n="name">0xA7F48AC1<!--String: "Off-the-Grid"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\OffTheGrid_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:644da44adacbfb55</T>
      <T n="text">0x36F59267<!--String: "The Off-the-Grid Lot Trait disconnects a lot from the utility grid. Most objects that require Power or Water will not work, supporting interesting new story themes and challenging gameplay elements. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\OffTheGrid_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:644da44adacbfb56</T>
      <T n="text">0xDE6FBCF6<!--String: "To apply the Off-the-Grid Lot Trait go into Build Mode and click on the Venue Info button in the top left corner. Open the Traits Panel from the pop-up menu. Then, click on the Off-the-Grid icon to slot it into your active lot. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\OffTheGrid_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:644da44adacbfb57</T>
      <T n="text">0xB2AD0E60<!--String: "Playing on an Off-the-Grid lot means access to new gameplay elements!\n\n• Click on a grill or Off-the-Grid supported oven to view exclusive recipes. Some require ingredients and provide powerful moodlets.\n• Water utility can be collected from various locations around the world.\n• Functional Off-the-Grid objects have unique interactions that allow them to fulfill needs.\n• Add Ice to supported Fridges. Just be sure to replace the ice before it melts!\n• Bills on Off-the-Grid lots do not charge for Water or Power utility. They also provide a Tax Break discount!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\OffTheGrid_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:644da44adacbfb50</T>
      <T n="text">0xD7674D09<!--String: "Items that support Off-the-Grid gameplay can be found in their own Off-the-Grid category in Build Mode. This section can be accessed within the Objects by Function drop down.\n\nAnywhere within Build Mode, Water and Power objects that have unique Off-the-Grid functionality are marked with a “Functional Off-the-Grid” tooltip note when you hover over them."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\OffTheGrid_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:644da44adacbfb51</T>
      <T n="text">0xB561A8FC<!--String: "When Power or Water utility is acquired as a surplus on an Off-the-Grid lot, Water and Power objects will function normally again.\n\nWhen this happens, a new interaction will appear on Functional Off-the-Grid objects to Turn On/Off Utility Usage. Toggling this option allows the player to determine which objects will pull from the excess utility and which will solely retain their Off-the-Grid functionality. "--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_LotSettings</E>
  </L>
